3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper presents an efficient decoding algorithm for partial spread codes, which is a topic in data structures and algorithms. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with network coding in the context of social and information networks. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the maximality of partial spread codes, which can be analyzed in terms of computational complexity.
